💔😢🙏🏻 A really, really hard thing to share, but far harder to do.

@medi.honey Thankyou my love. You know your heart always leaves me so touched and moved inside. I'm so thankful for you in my life and appreciate all you are💜💜💜

thank you. sending so much love and support your way, this is so huge and im genuinely weeping at this. weeping with love and respect and....perhaps joy is not the riiiiight word but something near. you deserve all the healing and safety and time you can get your hands on and SO much more. HUGE kudos to you in this, for allowing yourself this, for making it public and being so vulnerable. thank you, i love you, and i am forever in your corner interwebs or no💛💛💛🤟🤟
Love for you and big 👏👏👏 for your self love and setting boundaries ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

I’m so proud that you’ve created a chance to find things and do things and learn and know yourself. I’m so excited for the parts you find and choose to share, and I hope you find parts of yourself that are a quiet and silent joy you can hold for yourself away from social media.

@chronicleigh I appreciate that sentiment and am sorry you've had to know any version of trauma and loss ofself. My experience runs a bit different though as this began from the moment I was born, only existing at all to be part of an exploitation ring, an enslaved child, and truly never a person of my own. Ever. So, I'm going back to infancy and trying to figure me out -- something that's never happened in my life time. Starting from literal scratch is horrifying. I appreciate the compassion and empathy and hope you're on your feet.

as someone who has "shred" and destroyed all memories in the face of trauma, i completely and wholeheartedly understand. after having an abusive platonic relationship end, i suddenly couldnt engage with my interests from that time as they were contaminated with the memories of abuse. a few years after that, i had a nasty breakup with a boyfriend of mine. to stop myself from getting re-attached to him, and to let myself still enjoy the things i was into at the time, i shredded my memories of the time i knew him. that way i kept my interests without making myself sad by remembering him. i struggle to remember those parts of my life; i literally destroyed my own memory. if you ever want help, or just someone to scream about your troubles to, my inbox is always open. sending you lots of love and wishing you all the luck. 💖💖💖💖💖
❤️❤️Proud of you for taking care of yourself!
Praying that you find your true self and soul. I have a feeling you’re going to discover something beautiful. You have given so much. Accept the grace only God can give. It’s your time. .
Praying that you find your true self and soul. I have a feeling you’re going to discover something beautiful. You have given so much. Accept the grace only God can give. It’s your time. .
💗thank you for sharing. take all the time you need. you are deserving of healing! sending you supportive& healing thoughts 💫

Hey Kaa, you are amazing by letting us know you need this time and you do need, it will be hard but good for you. You know you have a lot of love here, from real people behind this screens, that you can reach out to at any time, and as we love you, we will respect your time and be proud of you for taking this decision. You deserve this rest. Deserve to get to know you better. We will be here, if you need, and sending a lot of hugs and love towards you!!

Recognizing you need a break and time to break is something incredibly hard and difficult to do, and the face your able to do so in and of itself is amazing. I’ll be sending you lots of love and positive vibes. 💜💙💓
I hope that you can focus on yourself. You deserve it 💜

Sending prayers and cheers of encouragement! Way to go!! I felt everything you said! I've felt that way for 43 1/2 years, & what bravery & power you unlocked for me! I'm literally so moved by this!! Thank you x a million!!!
Sending you love🖤 I'm here if you want a friend when you're ready🦓 be safe.
